<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 00:07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Illinois 94, Colorado 92  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOULDER, Colo. (AP) -- Chris Thunell scored 21 points as Southern
Illinois held on to defeat Colorado 94-92 in a first-round NIT game
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Jose Winston attempted a 3-point shot at the buzzer that would
have given Colorado the win, but the ball bounced off the back of
the rim.
</P>
<P>
   At end of the game, Colorado coach Ricardo Patton threw the ball
at one of the officials as he left the court and had to be
restrained by three people as he stormed after the referees.
</P>
<P>
   Five players scored in double figures for Colorado (18-14),
including Jamahl Mosley with a career-high 27 points, in the highly
physical game against Southern Illinois (20-12).
</P>
<P>
   The Salukis led 46-42 at the half, but Colorado took over 62-61
on a basket by Jaquay Walls with 13:17 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   The Salukis regained the lead for good on a 3-point basket by
Ricky Collum at 12:21 to start a 21-5 run that spanned the next
5:06.
</P>
<P>
   Southern Illinois finished the run with a basket by Thunell at
7:15 to give the Salukis their biggest lead, 82-67. Colorado
stormed back with an 18-4 run of their own including, seven points
each from Walls and Kyle Williams, to pull the Buffaloes within
86-85 with 1:41 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Thunell scored 6 of the last 8 points for Southern Illinois,
including four free throws, to help the Salukis hang on for the
victory.
</P>
<P>
   Collum finished with 14 points, while Kent Williams and Derrick
Tilmon each scored 12 for the Salukis, who shot 51.7 percent from
the field.
</P>
<P>
   Colorado's double-figure scorers were Walls with 18, Stephane
Pelle with 15, Will Smith with 12 and Kyle Williams with 10.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
