<HEADLINE> Texas Orders All Prisons Locked Down  </HEADLINE>
By MICHAEL GRACZYK, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- Texas' 86 prisons were locked down
indefinitely after an inmate was stabbed to death in the system's
latest major security breach.
</P>
<P>
   The order by the state's prisons chief means visitors are banned
and all 122,000 inmates are confined to their cells while
authorities search for weapons and other illegal items.
</P>
<P>
   The action in the nation's second-largest prison system came
after several incidents in which prisoners have been caught with
weapons or other illegal items. The number of attacks on guards
also has been escalating.
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, just seconds before his execution, convicted
murderer Ponchai Wilkerson spit out a handcuff key while strapped
to the death chamber gurney at the Huntsville prison.
</P>
<P>
   Last month, Wilkerson and another death row inmate, both armed
with makeshift weapons, held a guard hostage for 13 hours before
surrendering.
</P>
<P>
   In December, a guard was stabbed to death at the McConnell Unit.
</P>
<P>
   And Thursday morning, an inmate was fatally stabbed by another
prisoner at the Coffield Unit, authorities said. Roland Rios, 41,
was attacked with a homemade steel weapon while a guard escorted
him to a shower in handcuffs.
</P>
<P>
   ''When word came of the Coffield homicide, the decision was made
to lock down the entire system,'' said Larry Todd, a spokesman for
the Department of Criminal Justice. He added: ''It is unusual to
have a systemwide lockdown.''
</P>
<P>
   The last lockdown was ordered in 1998 after a hostage incident
at a prison in Abilene and an attempted escape by seven death row
inmates from the Ellis Unit. One inmate drowned in a creek nearby.
The others, Wilkerson among them, surrendered after guards began
shooting at them.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think it's a combination of a number of things: spring
cleaning, location of some contraband, the handcuff key, the
Coffield murder this morning,'' Todd said.
</P>
<P>
   All cells, cellblocks, recreation yards and work areas both
inside and outside prisons will be searched, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   ''If we find something that can be used as a weapon, we will
immediately seize it,'' Todd said. Todd said paper clips can be
braided into a spear, for example. Elastic removed from underwear
can be used to make a slingshot.
</P>
<P>
   The lockdown will last through this weekend and possibly through
the one after that, Todd said.
</P>
<P>
   The state's 26 jails and substance abuse units -- which hold
28,000 inmates -- will be searched but not locked down, and visitors
will be allowed.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: Texas corrections agency:
http://www.tdcj.state.tx.us
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-03-17-00 0113 </TRAILER>
