<HEADLINE> Stocks Open Lower; Dow Down 58  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices opened lower on Friday. The Dow
Jones Industrial Average is down 58 points in early trading. Losing
issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a seven-to-three lead
over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 10 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down two points.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street will have to put on quite a show to top Thursday's
performance.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow is coming off its biggest single-day gain ever, a
499-point advance on the heels of a 320-point gain Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Friday's session is beginning with a burst of trading activity.
</P>
<P>
   That's believed to be in connection with the triple-witching
session, the quarterly expiration of stock index futures, stock
index options and options on individual stocks.
</P>
<P>
   Investors also have more inflation news to consider -- a gain of
.05 percent in February's consumer price index.
</P>
</TEXT>
