<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded
heavily Friday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Boeing Co., up 1 9/16 at 37 3/16
</P>
<P>
   The plane maker said a tentative three-year agreement has been
reached with its engineers union, which, if ratified by the union,
could end a 38-day strike.
</P>
<P>
Carnival Corp., down 5 1/16 to 21 7/16
</P>
<P>
   The cruise operator said second-quarter earnings could be
''slightly lower'' than a year earlier because of slower booking
for its cruises. The company also said earnings for the second half
of fiscal 2000 will be 8 percent to 10 percent higher than a year
earlier. In addition, Carnival and Star Cruises canceled plans for
a joint takeover of Norwegian Cruise Lines
</P>
<P>
Interim Services, down 8 3/16 to 19\
</P>
<P>
   The human resources consulting company fell after analysts at
Wachovia Securities downgraded the stock to ''neutral'' from
''long-term buy'' because the company said it expects its first
quarter earnings to fall below Wall Street's expectations of 42
cents a share.
</P>
<P>
Tektronix Inc., up 2 7/16 to 66 15/16
</P>
<P>
   The company, which makes measuring equipment for high-tech
companies, rose after Goldman Sachs upgraded the stock to ''market
outperform'' from ''market perform.''
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Active Voice Corp., down 39 13/16 at 25 3/16
</P>
<P>
   The software company said it expects a loss of 50 cents to 70
cents a share in its fiscal fourth quarter. Analysts had expected
the company to earn 16 cents.
</P>
<P>
OSI Systems Inc., up 13 3/16 at 24 1/16
</P>
<P>
   The maker of X-ray inspection and metal detection systems said
it has developed a silicon-based fiber optic detector.
</P>
<P>
Applied Materials Inc., up 7 59/64 to 95 54/64
</P>
<P>
   Credit Suisse First Boston Inc. analysts said the maker of
semiconductor-production equipment will receive more new orders
this quarter than forecast by the company's management.
</P>
<P>
Biopure Corp., up 3| to 38~
</P>
<P>
   The drug company was rated ''buy'' in new coverage a Salomon
Smith Barney analyst.
</P>
