<HEADLINE> Excerpts From AP Buchanan Interview  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Excerpts from Reform Party
presidential
contender Patrick Buchanan in an interview Friday with The
Associated Press:
<TEXT>
<P>
   ''I'm out of the Republican Party for good.''
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   ''I think the Clinton White House, the Clinton-Gore
administration does not deserve to be reinstalled in power. But I
do not believe that the performance of the Republican establishment
in the last four years justifies their automatic claim to the White
House.''
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't think he's demonstrated the grasp of foreign policy or
international affairs that would justify putting the presidency of
the United States in his hands.''--On George W. Bush.
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   ''The vice president has had eight years in the White House.
That's as high quality experience as you can get.''--On Al Gore.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   ''The American electorate is more ready to roll the dice then it
has ever been in my lifetime. The allegiance to the two parties is
smaller than it's ever been. The willingness to take a look at a
third party is greater than it's ever been.''
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   ''I got back the word that he sort of welcomed me into the party
but he'd prefer not to have a phone call.'' -- On Ross Perot's
reaction to Buchanan's offer to talk before the conservative
columnist declared his presidential intentions.
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   ''We are going to reshape the party and we're going to meld our
people together with it, and what will come out will be populist,
traditionalist, conservative, very strongly supportive of the ideas
of mine on trade and foreign policy and immigration policy. ... At
the end it'll look like the Rockettes.''
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   ''Whenever I hear the word 'collectivism' I release the safety
clip from my revolver. Look, I'm not in a political collective. I
have not altered my views on a single issue with the exception of
adding one issue ... expanding the electorate.''
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   ''These folks haven't killed anybody down there. I agree with
them on all manner of social and cultural issues. ... And frankly,
I don't like the idea of everybody in this city and the media and
everything else piling on this little school because they hold
views that none of us happen to share.''--On Bob Jones University.
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   ''They claim that policy goes back to their interpretation of
the Old Testament. It's not my interpretation.''-- On whether he
agrees with Bob Jones University's former ban on interracial
dating.
</P>
</TEXT>
