<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 18:40 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> E-ZPass on New Jersey Turnpike system off until August  </HEADLINE>
By RALPH SIEGEL, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) -- New Jersey Turnpike commuters hoping
electronic E-ZPass technology would get them past long lines at
toll plazas on hot summer days will have to wait.
</P>
<P>
   The electronic sensor system, scheduled to be in place May 22,
will not be ready until Aug. 1 at the earliest, according to
turnpike authority director Edward Gross. And even the postponed
date remains uncertain.
</P>
<P>
   Gross said there have been construction delays in setting up
specific toll booths with the sensor equipment and surveillance
cameras needed for the E-ZPass system to work properly. He said the
prime contractor, Adesta Transportation, formerly MFS Technologies,
reported it would have about 84 of the 157 toll lanes ready by the
deadline.
</P>
<P>
   Gross said turnpike officials decided this was not adequate and
could create traffic hazards and confusion. He said Adesta believes
it could have 140 E-ZPass lanes ready to go on Aug. 1.
</P>
<P>
   ''There was a slippage in the construction schedule, and last
week we took a very, very good look at the progress of
construction,'' Gross said. ''Our conclusion was that we could not
make May 22 and deliver a quality system that would work
efficiently and safely.''
</P>
<P>
   ''Just the testing alone for this system is going to be at least
30 days,'' Gross said.
</P>
<P>
   The silver lining to the delay is that a scheduled toll increase
of 20 percent on the turnpike will not begin until E-ZPass is up
and running.
</P>
<P>
   Gross said it is important to make sure the electronic toll
systems work perfectly before the E-ZPass system makes its debut
because if there are problems, commuters will lose confidence in
E-ZPass and will not sign up for it.
</P>
<P>
   That sort of damage to trust would be difficult to recover. ''It
would represent a tremendous setback in the advancement of
electronic toll collection,'' Gross said.
</P>
<P>
   E-ZPass tolls are in place at all of the crossings into New
York, on the Atlantic City Expressway and at northern toll plazas
on the Garden State Parkway from Union to Bergen counties.
</P>
<P>
   But Gross said the turnpike is a different matter because
E-ZPass cannot be implemented at a single toll point.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're opening all at one time, 28 plazas, 157 lanes, and they
all have to work and integrate with each other, and work
perfectly,'' Gross said.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   http://www.state.nj.us/turnpike
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
