<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 19:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US, Ghana Sign Aviation Agreement  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The United States and the West African nation
of Ghana signed an open skies agreement, Transportation Secretary
Rodney Slater announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The pact, signed on Thursday, will eliminate all restrictions on
air service between the two nations over the next six years.
Restrictions on air cargo services and airline pricing are to be
removed immediately.
</P>
<P>
   The move represents the first formal aviation tie between the
two nations, and the fourth of its kind between the United States
and an African nation. The U.S. has forty-four such agreements in
all.
</P>
</TEXT>
