<HEADLINE> Greek Fisherman Finds Son's Body  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATHENS, Greece (AP) -- A fisherman made a tragic discovery when
he hauled in his fishing nets Friday, finding the body of his son
who had been missing for a month, the merchant marine ministry
said.
</P>
<P>
   Panagiotis Vettas, 22, fell overboard on Jan. 26 during a
fishing trip with his 60-year-old father, Giorgos, southeast of the
Kimolos Island, 90 miles southwest of Athens.
</P>
<P>
   Rescue crews and the coast guard were unable to locate him, and
the search was called off after a few days, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   But as Giorgos Vettas hauled in his fishing nets Friday off the
coast of an Aegean island near where his son had disappeared, he
found they contained the remains of his son.
</P>
<P>
   The body was being examined by a coroner, and port police were
investigating the case.
</P>
