<HEADLINE> Cleveland Gun Lawsuit To Proceed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND (AP) -- A federal judge has ruled that the city of
Cleveland may proceed with its lawsuit against the gun industry.
</P>
<P>
   The ruling was issued Tuesday by U.S. District Court Judge
Donald C. Nugent, who rejected a gun-industry request to dismiss
the lawsuit.
</P>
<P>
   James Dorr, an attorney representing the gun industry, said
Friday that no decision had been made whether to appeal.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, the city sued gun makers to try to force the industry
to share the cost of police, ambulance and hospital services needed
because of gun-related violence.
</P>
<P>
   The industry said gun makers should not be held accountable for
criminal use of a legal product.
</P>
