<HEADLINE> Lightning 3, Devils 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Rich Parent made 34 saves as the
Tampa Bay Lightning extended their unbeaten streak to three Friday
night with a 3-1 victory over the New Jersey Devils, who clinched a
playoff spot despite the loss.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Johnson, Fredrik Modin and Todd Warriner scored for Tampa
Bay, which won for only the second time at Continental Airlines
Arena (2-15-1).
</P>
<P>
   Claude Lemieux scored for the Eastern Conference-leading Devils,
who have won only two of their last eight contests (2-5-1). New
Jersey was assured of a playoff berth Friday thanks to the Carolina
Hurricanes' 4-2 loss to the Washington Capitals.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson scored the only goal of the first period on a
semi-breakaway at 2:58. Johnson beat Martin Brodeur with a high
shot to the glove side.
</P>
<P>
   Modin extended the Lightning lead to 2-0 at 3:27 of the second
period with an unassisted goal. Sergei Nemchinov turned the puck
over to Modin in the neutral zone. He made the Devils pay for the
mistake by drilling a wrist shot past Brodeur from the high slot.
</P>
<P>
   The Devils broke through against Parent at 7:55 of the second as
Lemieux knocked in a rebound of a Nemchinov shot.
</P>
<P>
   Parent held the Devils off in the third with 11 saves, including
a spectacular diving stop against Lemieux with 14 minutes
remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Warriner sealed the win on a power-play goal with 39.4 seconds
remaining.
</P>
