<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 23:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bomb Threat Evacuates French Theater  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PARIS (AP) -- Police evacuated a theater where the Vienna
Philharmonic orchestra was performing Friday after receiving a bomb
threat.
</P>
<P>
   Music-lovers and musicians had to leave the Theatre des
Champs-Elysees halfway through the program of music by Brahms but
they were allowed back some 30 minutes later after police searched
the theater and declared it safe.
</P>
<P>
   Police did not give any further details of the threat.
</P>
<P>
   Before the concert began, the audience was given leaflets in
which the orchestra distanced itself from ''racist'' remarks of
Austria's far-right Freedom Party.
</P>
<P>
   The arts in Austria have become embroiled in the controversy
surrounding the entry of the Freedom Party into the country's
governing coalition.
</P>
<P>
   Austria has been politically isolated in Europe since the
Freedom Party, formerly headed by Joerg Haider, entered the
coalition government in February.
</P>
<P>
   The outrage stems from Haider's opposition to immigration and
rapid European Union expansion, as well as previous statements
praising some Nazi policies. He has since apologized for those
comments.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-03-17-00 2310 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
