<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-17 23:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank One cutting 5,100 Jobs  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Bank One Corp. is cutting 5,100 jobs in its
credit card, consumer lending and staff services divisions, the
company said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The job cuts represent about 6 percent of the company's work
force, said spokesman Tom Kelly. The company had warned of the job
cuts in January but had not made public the number, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Chicago-based Bank One, the fourth-largest U.S. bank, disclosed
the cuts in its annual report filed with the Securities and
Exchange Commission.
</P>
<P>
   Kelly said more than half of the jobs have been cut since
January through elimination or attrition, and the rest will be cut
over the next year. Many of the employees will find jobs in other
areas of the company, he said.
</P>
<P>
   He said the cuts were focused in the credit card, consumer
lending and staff units so the company can concentrate on its
primary markets in 14 states.
</P>
<P>
   Bank One earlier this month announced that ''weak''
first-quarter earnings may fall below analysts' expectations. The
bank's problems stem from its First USA unit, the nation's No. 2
issuer of credit cards behind Citibank.
</P>
<P>
   Its stock has fallen by more than half since the announcement
last August that First USA's once-soaring growth had fallen off,
the victim of squeezed profit margins and issuing too many
low-interest cards.
</P>
<P>
   About 1,000 of the eliminated jobs were in the credit card
division.
</P>
<P>
   Bank One shares fell [ to 27| on the New York Stock Exchange on
Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
