<HEADLINE> Wrong Number Listed in Ramsey's Book  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- A new book by the parents of JonBenet Ramsey has a
wrong number listed for people to call with information about the
slaying.
</P>
<P>
   The number listed in ''The Death of Innocence'' written by John
and Patsy Ramsey and released Friday, rings into the house of Craig
Swan of Littleton.
</P>
<P>
   The book's publisher, Thomas Nelson Publishing, could not be
reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   A message left on Swan's answering machine was not returned.
</P>
<P>
   JonBenet Ramsey was found dead in her parent's Boulder home on
Dec. 26, 1996. A 13-month grand jury investigation ended in October
without any indictments.
</P>
<P>
   The correct tip line number is (720) 904-3739.
</P>
</TEXT>
