<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nuggets 114, Clippers 87  </HEADLINE>
By JOHN MOSSMAN, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Antonio McDyess had 23 points and Raef LaFrentz
21, helping the Denver Nuggets snap a seven-game losing streak with
a 114-87 victory Friday night over the Los Angeles Clippers.
</P>
<P>
   McDyess, benched four minutes into the game by an angry coach
Dan Issel for not playing defense, had all of his points after
returning to the game late in the first quarter. He also had 15
rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   LaFrentz had eight rebounds and six blocked shots, and rookie
James Posey added 16 points, eight rebounds and three steals.
</P>
<P>
   Maurice Taylor led the Clippers with 21 points, and Derek
Anderson had 11.
</P>
<P>
   Denver, leading 54-50 at intermission, shot 53 percent in the
third quarter compared to Los Angeles' 35 percent to take an 87-73
lead into the final period.
</P>
<P>
   Charles R. Jones cut the deficit to 12 points early in the
fourth quarter, but McDyess hit four baskets in the next 2:16 and
Denver expanded its lead to 99-80 with 5:29 to go.
</P>
<P>
   Taylor's reverse layup gave the Clippers a 9-5 lead early in the
game. Denver had shot just 1-for-7 from the floor to that point,
and during a timeout with 8:17 left in the quarter, Issel told his
star forward to take a seat.
</P>
<P>
   The Nuggets responded with a 13-2 run, including back-to-back
slam dunks by LaFrentz and consecutive 3-pointers by Chris Gatling.
LaFrentz had 12 points in the quarter as Denver took a 30-21 lead.
</P>
<P>
   McDyess, who returned to the lineup with 1:37 left in the
opening quarter, hit a 12-foot jumper two minutes into the second
period, giving Denver a 37-24 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Taylor then had eight points during a 19-8 flurry that drew the
Clippers within two, 45-43. Taylor had 13 points in the quarter and
17 at the half.
</P>
<P>
   Nick Van Exel's 3-pointer, McDyess' slam and LaFrentz's layup
gave Denver a 61-52 lead early in the third period. Eric Piatkowski
hit a 3-pointer, but Posey then had four of the Nuggets' next six
points, and the Clippers got no closer than nine points after
that.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Before the game, the Clippers activated center Keith Closs
from the injured list. Closs had missed the previous five games
with back spasms. The Clippers also waived forward Mario Bennett,
who was signed to a 10-day contract on March 7. ... Denver's Tariq
Abdul-Wahad, who had missed the previous six games with a sprained
left wrist, played sparingly and appeared to aggravate the injury.
... The Nuggets' seven-game skid was their longest of the season.
</P>
</TEXT>
